Khartoum, Mr.4 (SUNA) - Foreign Minister, Ibrahim Ghandour received, Sunday, copies of credentials of the non-resident Ambassador of Portugal, Cyprus, Greece, Myanmar, Malawi, Finland and Ghana, prior to submitting their original copies to the President of the Republic. The Minister, then met with the delegation of ambassadors of the non-resident representation countries to Sudan in the presence of the honorary consuls of those countries, where he briefed them on the economic and political situations in Sudan, investment opportunities and the regional and international roles of Sudan to support peace, stability and security principles in addition to, promotion of the international, mutual cooperation program. The minister has affirmed Sudan's concern over strengthening relations with all countries, referring that Sudan enjoys distinguished relations with all the non-resident representation countries, expressing his ministry's readiness to facilitate the diplomats' missions in the country.